INTRODUCTION

This is a ML project using GDC data (https://portal.gdc.cancer.gov/repository) to train a model for cancer prediction. 
All cancers are classified according to primary site.

ENVIRONMENT

python3, pandas, numpy, sklearn, matplotlib are required.
use following command to install these modules

pip3 install pandas numpy sklearn matplotlib

HOW TO RUN

1. cd src
2. run check.py 
   check data file integrity
3. run parse_file_case_id.py
   generate relationship between file_id and case_id
4. run request_meta.py
   download meta data for file and case 
5. run gen_miRNA_matrix.py
   generate miRNA and primary site (label) matrix
6. run predict.py
   train and evaluate model

